    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1855-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1855-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="158" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d158">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[504]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">McCoy</persName>, district attorney.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Executive
                                    Mansion</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1855-12-26">
                        <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 26,
                                    1855</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas S. McCoy</hi>,
                                    Esq.,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States District Attorney, New
                                    Orleans, Louisiana:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Your letter of the 18th instant, addressed to the Attorney-General,
                                has been submitted to me. Your call upon the collector is fully
                                approved. Continue to act in the premises with the utmost energy and
                                vigilance. You are hereby empowered to exercise all such authority
                                in this relation over the public force as the President may lawfully
                                delegate by virtue of the eighth section of the act of Congress of
                                April 20, 1818.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRANKLIN PIERCE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
